@startuml Sequence_Connect_Bank
title Connect Bank Account

actor User
participant "Next.js\nFrontend" as FE
participant "tRPC API" as API
participant "PlaidLink\nService" as PLS
participant "Plaid API" as Plaid
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
queue "BullMQ" as Queue

User -> FE: Clicks "Connect Bank"
FE -> API: plaid.createLinkToken()
API -> PLS: createLinkToken(userId)
PLS -> Plaid: POST /link/token/create
Plaid --> PLS: link_token
PLS --> API: linkToken
API --> FE: linkToken

FE -> FE: Opens Plaid Link modal
User -> FE: Selects institution,\nauthenticates
FE -> Plaid: (Plaid Link SDK flow)
Plaid --> FE: public_token + metadata

FE -> API: plaid.exchangeToken(publicToken, metadata)
API -> PLS: exchangePublicToken(userId, publicToken, metadata)
PLS -> Plaid: POST /item/public_token/exchange
Plaid --> PLS: access_token + item_id

PLS -> DB: INSERT plaid_item\n(status: Active, cursor: "")
PLS -> DB: INSERT accounts\n(from metadata)
PLS -> Queue: Enqueue "initial-sync"\njob(plaidItemId)
PLS --> API: PlaidItem
API --> FE: { success: true, item }
FE --> User: "Bank connected!\nSyncing transactions..."

Queue -> Queue: Worker picks up\n"initial-sync" job

note right of Queue
  The initial sync job triggers
  TransactionSyncService which
  is covered in the next sequence
  diagram.
end note

@enduml
